{"parse":{"title":"potato","pageid":37487,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n[[Image:Potato and cross section.jpg|thumb|right|250 px|An intact '''potato''' (vegetable, on the right) and a cross-section of a second potato]]\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|potatoe||archaic|now|nonstandard}}\n* {{alter|en|p'tater|tater||dialectal or informal}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|en|es|patata}}, itself borrowed from {{der|en|tnq|batata||[[sweet potato]]}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|pə-tāʹtō}}, {{rhymes|en|eɪtəʊ|s=3}}\n* {{IPA|en|/pəˈteɪ.təʊ/|a=England}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-potato.ogg|a=RP|IPA=[pə̥ˈtʰɛɪ̯θ͇ɜɵ]}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Nattes à chat-potato.wav|a=RP|IPA=[pə̥ˈtʰɛi̯tʰɜʊ̈]}}\n* {{IPA|en|/pəˈteɪ.toʊ/|[-ˈteɪ.ɾoʊ]|a=North America}}, {{q|colloquial, sometimes}} {{IPAchar|/pəˈteɪ.tə/}}<ref>{{R:Collins}}</ref><ref>{{R:MWO}}</ref>\n** {{audio|en|en-us-potato.ogg|a=US|IPA=[pə̥ˈtʰeˑɾo]}}\n* {{IPA|en|/pɵˈʈaʈo/|/pɵˈʈeʈo/|a=Indic}}, {{rhymes|en|ætəʊ|eɪtəʊ|s=3}}\n* {{IPA|en|/poˈteɪ.to/|a=Philippines}}\n* {{IPA|en|/pəˈteto/|a=Scotland}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~|es}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q16587531}} A plant of species {{taxfmt|Solanum tuberosum|species}} or its edible [[starchy]] [[tuber]].\n#: {{syn|en|potater|tato|tater}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|title=Condensed Replies to Various Letters|editor=Leroy M[ilton] Yale| journal=Babyhood: The Mother’s Nursery Guide, Devoted to the Care of Children| volume=VII| location=New York, N.Y.; London| publisher=Babyhood Publishing Company| year=1891| page=230| column=2| passage=Do not let your child have '''potato''' for another year; he will probably take milk well enough after he is weaned.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=C[harles] F[ord] Langworthy; Caroline L[ouisa] Hunt|title=Cheese and Its Economical Uses in the Diet|series=[[w:Farmers' Bulletin|Farmers’ Bulletin]] 487|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[w:United States Government Publishing Office|Government Printing Office]]| year=1912| page=24| pageurl=https://archive.org/details/CAT87202469/page/24/mode/1up|passage=The protein value of this dish is equal to that of 1⅛ pounds of '''potato''' and beef, the fuel value, however, being much in excess of these.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=Annual Report of the Local Government Board for Scotland| year=1915| page=17| passage=A number of the children said that they had '''potato''' for breakfast, '''potato''' and herring for dinner, '''potato''' and milk for supper.}}\n#* '''1917''', {{w|Knut Hamsun}}, ''{{w|Growth of the Soil}}'', Book 1, [[s:Growth_of_the_Soil/Book_1/Chapter_4|Ch.4]], at p.34:\n#*: What was that about '''potatoes'''? Were they just a thing from foreign parts, like coffee; a luxury, an extra? Oh, the potato is a lordly fruit; drought or downpour, it grows and grows all the same. It laughs at the weather, and will stand anything; only deal kindly with it, and it yields fifteen-fold again. [...] A man may lack grain to make bread, but give him potatoes and he will not starve. Roast them in embers, and there is supper; boil them in water, and there's a breakfast ready.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author={{w|Harry E. Wedeck}}|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=195|passage=Although the '''potato''' actually has no exciting value, it was believed, in the seventeenth century, to possess definite aphrodisiac qualities, and is frequent mentioned in this respect in Elizabethan drama.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Climate Change and the Health of Nations|author=Anthony J. McMichael; Alistair Woodward; Cameron Muir|year=2017|ISBN=9780190262952|page=213| passage='''Potatoes''' were introduced to Ireland in 1590 after being brought to Europe by Spanish conquistadores from their place of origin in the South American Andes.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2021 December 1|author=Nigel Harris|title=St Pancras and King's Cross: 1947| journal=RAIL| issue=945| page=42| text=The rocketing popularity of '''potatoes''' in London's diet led to the conversion of the temporary GNR passenger station north of the canal [...] as a dedicated '''potato''' terminal, whose significant traffic was stolen from coastal shipping.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[sweet potato]] ({{taxfmt|Ipomoea batatas|species}}).\n# {{lb|en|informal|UK}} A [[conspicuous]] [[hole]] in a [[sock]] or [[stocking]].\n#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1943|author={{w|Agatha Christie}}|title=The Moving Finger|chapter=|url=|page=|text=She was untidily dressed as usual and there were '''potatoes''' in both heels.}}\n# A [[person]] or [[animal]] shaped like a potato, that is, with a large [[belly]] and/or short legs.\n# {{n-g|Metaphor for a person or thing of little value.}}\n#* {{RQ:Smollett Reprisal|scene=ii|page=8|passage=I don't value Monſieur de Champignon a rotten '''potatoe'''; {{...}}}}\n## {{lb|en|slang|offensive}} A [[mentally]] [[handicapped]] [[person]].\n## {{lb|en|humorous}} A [[camera]] that takes [[poor]]-[[quality]] [[picture]]s or [[video]]s.\n## {{lb|en|humorous|slang|computing}} An [[underpowered]] [[computer]] or other [[device]], especially when [[small]] in [[size]].<!--may relate to the \"potato-powered Web server\" hoax-->\n##* {{quote-journal|en|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/overwatch-community-donates-pc-parts-to-fan-who-could-barely-run-it-at-800x600/| date=2017-03-17| author=Steven Messner| title=Overwatch community donates PC parts to fan who could barely run it at 800x600| journal=PC Gamer| passage=When most people refer to their computers as a '''potato''' they're being hyperbolic, but not Ethan. He plays Overwatch at 800x600 resolution with all settings on low and is excited when he gets 30 fps.}}\n##* {{quote-journal|en|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-09-22-meet-the-people-making-music-with-mega-drives-and-guitars-from-game-boys| date=2019-09-22| author=Benjamin Burns| title=Meet the people making music with Mega Drives, Game Boys and gAtaris| journal=Eurogamer| passage=If you want to have a go right now, then Famitracker will let you compose songs for the NES and it'll run on a Windows-operated '''potato'''.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|plant}} {{l|en|p'tater}} {{q|dialectal}}, {{l|en|spud}} {{qualifier|slang}}, {{l|en|tater}} {{q|Britain|US|informal}}, {{l|en|tatie}} {{q|Scotland, Cumbria, dialect}}, {{l|en|tator}} {{q|eye dialect}}\n* {{sense|vegetable}} {{l|en|Donovan}} {{q|archaic slang}}, {{l|en|earthapple}} {{qualifier|rare}}, {{l|en|murphy}}, {{l|en|bog orange}} {{q|obsolete slang}}, {{l|en|Irish apricot}} {{q|obsolete slang}}, {{l|en|Irish fruit}} {{q|obsolete slang}}, {{l|en|mickey}}\n* {{sense|low-end computer}} {{l|en|toaster}} {{q|slang}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n| [[air potato]], {{vern|air-potato}} ({{taxfmt|Dioscorea bulbifera|species}})|all that and a bag of potato chips|almond potato|Amandine potato|Andean potato|{{taxlink|Andean potato latent virus|species}}|{{taxlink|Andean potato mottle virus|species}}|{{vern|Andean potato weevil}} ({{taxlink|Premnotrypes|genus}} spp.)|Anna potatoes\n| baked potato|baking potato|Bengal potatoes|Bintje potato|blue potato|boiling potato|Bordet-Gengou potato blood agar|Burbank potato,Burbank Russet potato|{{vern|bastard potato}}|{{vern|Brazilian potato tree}} ({{taxlink|Solanum wrightii|species}})\n| Canarian wrinkly potatoes|{{vern|Caribe potato}} ({{taxfmt|Solanum tuberosum|species}})|{{vern|Carolina potato}} ({{taxfmt|Solanum tuberosum|species}})|chat potatoes|chef's potato|{{vern|Chilean potato-tree}}, {{vern|Chilean potato vine}} ({{taxlink|Solanum crispum|species}})|{{vern|Chinese potato}} ({{taxlink|Plectranthus rotundifolius|species}}, {{taxlink|Coleus rotundifolius|species}})|chipped potato|clean potato|cold-potato routing|{{vern|coleus potato}} ({{taxlink|Coleus rotundifolius|species}})|[[Colorado potato beetle]] ({{taxfmt|Leptinotarsa decemlineata|species}})|couch potato|{{vern|country potato}} ({{taxlink|Coleus rotundifolius|species}})|Cree potato|Cuban sweet potato\n| Delmonico potato|desk potato|drop like a hot potato|duchess potatoes,duchesse potatoes|[[duck potato]] ({{taxlink|Sagittaria latifolia|species}})\n| Eskimo potato\n| [[false potato beetle]] ({{taxlink|Leptinotarsa juncta|species}})|fauxtato|fingerling potato|finger potato|fondante potato|fondant potato|frafra potato|French-fried potatoes|french fried potato,French fried potato,French-fried potato,french-fried potato\n| {{vern|giant potato creeper}} ({{taxlink|Solanum wendlandii|species}})|{{vern|glasshouse and potato aphid}}, {{vern|glasshouse-potato aphid}} ({{taxlink|Aulacorthum solani|species}})|Goa potato|Greenfield potatoes|green potato\n| {{vern|Hausa potato}} ({{taxlink|Coleus rotundifolius|species}})|hog potato,hog's potato|home-fried potatoes|hot potato|hot-potato routing|potato tot\n| [[Indian potato]] ({{taxlink|Sagittaria latifolia|species}}, ({{taxlink|Apios americana|species}})|Irish potato\n| jacket potato|{{vern|Japanese potato}} ({{taxfmt|Colocasia antiquorum|species}})|Japanese sweet potato|Jersey Royal potatoes|Jerusalem potato\n| kidney potato\n| little potato|Livingstone potato|long white potato|Lyonnaise potatoes\n| {{vern|Madagascar potato}} ({{taxlink|Plectranthus rotundifolius|species}})|Maori potato|mashed potato,mashed potatoes|mash potato|meat and potatoes|{{vern|Mexican potato}} ({{taxlink|Pachyrhizus erosus|species}})|mouse potato\n| {{vern|native potato}} ({{taxlink|Coleus rotundifolius|species}})|new potato|nonpotato\n| O'Brien potatoes|{{vern|oca potato}} ({{taxlink|Oxalis tuberosa|species}})|Okinawan purple potato|Okinawan sweet potato|one potato, two potato\n| pineapple potato|pomato|potater\n| [[potato aphid]] ({{taxlink|Macrosiphum euphorbiae|species}})|potato apple bread|potato apple,potato-apple|{{taxlink|Potato aucuba mosaic virus|species}}\n| potato badger|potato-ball|[[potato bean]], {{vern|potato-bean}} ({{taxlink|Apios americana|species}})|[[potato beetle]], {{vern|potato-beetle}}|{{taxlink|Potato black ringspot virus|species}}|potato blight|potato blood agar|potato-bogle|potato-box|potato bread|[[potato bug]], {{vern|potato-bug}}|potato bush\n| potato cake,potato-cake|potato cannon|potato chaser|potato chip|potato chip of the sea|potato chips|potato clay|potato cod|{{vern|potato creeper}}|potato crisp,potato crisps|potato curl|potato cyst|{{vern|potato cyst nematode}} ({{taxlink|Globodera|genus}} spp.)\n| {{taxlink|Potato deforming mosaic virus|species}}|potato dextrose agar|potato dextrose broth|potato digger|potato dumpling\n| potatoe|potato-eater,potato eater|{{vern|potato eelworm}}, {{vern|potato eel}} ({{taxlink|Globodera rostochiensis|species}})|potatoes and point|potatoey|potato-eye\n| potato failure|potato family|potato famine|{{vern|potato farls}}|{{vern|potato fern}}|potato finger|potato flake|potato flour|[[potato fly]], {{vern|potato-fly}} ({{taxlink|Epicauta vittata|species|wplink=0}})|potato fork|{{vern|potato fungus}} ({{taxfmt|Phytophthora infestans|species}})\n| potato grant|potato gun\n| potato-headed|potato head,potato-head|potato hook\n| potato in its jacket\n| potato-jaw\n| potato kugel\n| potato late blight|{{taxlink|Potato latent virus|species}}|potato latke|{{taxlink|Potato leafroll virus|species}}|{{vern|potato leafhopper}} ({{taxlink|Empoasca fabae|species}})|potato lectin|potatoless|potatolike|potato-loaf\n| potato masher,potato-masher|{{vern|potato mildew}} ({{taxfmt|Phytophthora infestans|species}})|potato-mill|potato mold,potato mould|potato mosaic|{{taxlink|Potato mop-top virus|species}}|[[potato moth]] ({{taxlink|Stoeberhinus testaceus|species}})|potato-mouth|potato-mouthed|potato murrain\n| potatoness|potato nigger|potato nose,potato-nose|potato nuggets\n| potato oat|potato of Canada|potato oil|potato onion|potato opening\n| potato pancake|potato paradox|potato patch|potato peel|potato peeler,potato-peeler|potato peelings|potato pen|potato-phile,potatophile|potato pie|potato pit|potato plant|Potato Point|potato pretender|[[potato psyllid]] ({{taxlink|Bactericer