he Raw Files: 1998|page=26\n|passage=Bradshaw doesn't find much humour in it though, and beats the tar out of Dustin, '''potatoing''' him with every blow.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To hit with a thrown or fired potato.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2017|author=A. J. Low|title=Sherlock Sam’s Orange Shorts: Special Edition\n|passage=Yvonne and Lee Swee '''potatoed''' Deputy Lestrade multiple times before Sheriff Moran '''potatoed''' them both. {{...}} Suddenly, Sheriff Moran heard the ''click click'' of an empty weapon. He turned to see that both Mayor Eliza and Kat had run out of ammunition.}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|onomatopoeia|often repeated}} The [[rhythmic]] [[sound]] produced by a [[V-twin]] engine—a distinctive [[deep]], [[throaty]] [[exhaust]] note.\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aooptt|patoot|topato}}\n\n{{cln|en|nouns with irregular plurals}}\n{{C|en|People|Potatoes}}\n\n==Ido==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|io|es|tnq}}\n{{bor+|io|en|potato}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{io-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|io|ato}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{io-noun|potat}}\n\n# [[#English|potato]]\n#: {{syn|io|terpomo}}\n\n{{C|io|Nightshades|Vegetables}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr}}\n\n===Participle===\n{{it-pp}}\n\n# {{past participle of|it|potare}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|it|a=aooptt|optato|topato}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA|pōtātō}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form|head=pōtātō}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|pōtō||2//3|s|futr|actv|impr}}\n\n===Participle===\n{{head|la|participle form|head=pōtātō}}\n\n# {{infl of|la|pōtātus||mn|dat//abl|s}}"}}